research_municipality_step.notes: The City of Seminole, TX operates under a Home Rule form of government with a City Council consisting of a Mayor and five council members. While four council members and the Mayor are identified, the name of the fifth council member was not explicitly found in the provided search results. The specific districts for each council member were also not available. One source indicated that three council members are elected and two are appointed by the Mayor, while the official city website implies all five council members are part of the elected governing body.
